Sentencas: The sintered NiO-Fe2O3 composites are consisted of NiO and NiFe2O4, and are fully reducible to porous metallic Ni-Fe alloys in H-2 at temperatures between 600 and 750 degrees C.

Sentencas: The porous structure contains pores in bimodal distribution with larger pores between the sintered particles and smaller ones inside the particles.

Sentencas: The oxidation resistance of the Ni-Fe alloy anode supports at 600 and 750 degrees C is increased by the addition of Fe, their oxidation kinetics obeys a multistage parabolic law in the form of (Percentage weight gain/Specific surface area) (2) = kp.t, where k(p) is the rate constant and t the oxidation time.
Titulo: Porous Ni-Fe alloys as anode support for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells: I. Fabrication, redox and thermal behaviors

Sentencas: The dimension of the Ni-Fe anode supports is slightly changed without disintegrating their structure, and Fe addition is beneficial to the redox stability.
